==English==

===Etymology===
from [[cut]] "to remove" + [[red tape]] "excessive bureaucratic procedures"

===Verb phrase===
'''to cut red tape''' (cuts red tape, cutting red tape)

#US American idiom for ''to reduce [[bureaucracy]]''.
#: This one insurance company that I know of, is an expert at '''cutting red tape''' to process your claim faster.

